six riders\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1555}, {\"ngram\": \"each heat\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1588}, {\"ngram\": \"the quarter-finals\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1636}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Twelve reach the semi-finals and an elite six battle it out in the medal final.\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1717, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the semi\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 1659}, {\"ngram\": \"finals\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1666}, {\"ngram\": \"an elite six battle\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1690}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal final\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1716}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those who do not make the cut in the first round have a second chance in the repechage round, where the top two finishers from four heats of five riders can keep their medal dreams alive.\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1906, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the cut\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1748}, {\"ngram\": \"the first round\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1767}, {\"ngram\": \"a second chance\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1788}, {\"ngram\": \"the repechage round\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1811}, {\"ngram\": \"the top two finishers\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1840}, {\"ngram\": \"four heats\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1856}, {\"ngram\": \"five riders\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"their medal dreams\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1899}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The omnium event in track cycling is slightly more complex as teams accumulate points across four different formats: the scratch race, tempo race, elimination race and the points race.\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 2094, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The omnium event\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1926}, {\"ngram\": \"track cycling\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1943}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 1972, \"to\": 1977}, {\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 1995}, {\"ngram\": \"four different formats\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2025}, {\"ngram\": \"the scratch race\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2043}, {\"ngram\": \"tempo race\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2055}, {\"ngram\": \"elimination race\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2073}, {\"ngram\": \"the points race\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the scratch, tempo and elimination races, riders earn 40 points for coming first, 38 points for second place, 36 points for third, and so on.\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2240, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the scratch\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2110}, {\"ngram\": \"tempo\", \"from\": 2112, \"to\": 2117}, {\"ngram\": \"elimination races\", \"from\": 2122, \"to\": 2139}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2147}, {\"ngram\": \"40 points\", \"from\": 2153, \"to\": 2162}, {\"ngram\": \"38 points\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2190}, {\"ngram\": \"second place\", \"from\": 2195, \"to\": 2207}, {\"ngram\": \"36 points\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2218}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Men are required to complete 40 laps while women must complete 30; however, this increases to 100 laps for men and 80 laps for women in the points race.\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2393, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Men\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2244}, {\"ngram\": \"40 laps\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2289}, {\"ngram\": \"100 laps\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2343}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2351}, {\"ngram\": \"80 laps\", \"from\": 2356, \"to\": 2363}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2373}, {\"ngram\": \"the points race\", \"from\": 2377, \"to\": 2392}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The points race also has a different points system, awarding five points for first place, three points for second, two points for third and one point for fourth.\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2556, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The points race\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2410}, {\"ngram\": \"a different points system\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2445}, {\"ngram\": \"five points\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2467}, {\"ngram\": \"first place\", \"from\": 2472, \"to\": 2483}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The final sprint offers double points - and it's important to note that any rider who laps the field earns an extra 20 points, while being lapped results in a 20-point penalty.\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2733, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The final sprint\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2573}, {\"ngram\": \"double points\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2594}, {\"ngram\": \"any rider\", \"from\": 2629, \"to\": 2638}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 2648, \"to\": 2657}, {\"ngram\": \"an extra 20 points\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2682}, {\"ngram\": \"results\", \"from\": 2703, \"to\": 2710}, {\"ngram\": \"a 20-point penalty\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Madison is a two-person relay that can get very confusing.\", \"from\": 2737, \"to\": 2799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2741, \"end\": 2748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_National_Madison_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9651016533664526, \"rank\": 0.03616028064171164, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_National_Madison_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_National_Madison_Championships\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a two-person relay\", \"from\": 2752, \"to\": 2770}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One rider actively competes while their partner remains inactive at the top of the track.\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2889, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One rider\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2809}, {\"ngram\": \"their partner\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 2847}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2875}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 2888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team-mates alternate between racing and resting, with points awarded in intermediate sprints every 10 laps.\", \"from\": 2891, \"to\": 2998, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 2945, \"to\": 2951}, {\"ngram\": \"intermediate sprints\", \"from\": 2963, \"to\": 2983}, {\"ngram\": \"every 10 laps\", \"from\": 2984, \"to\": 2997}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's Madison spans 200 laps (around 31 miles) while the women's race covers only 120 laps (roughly 18.5 miles), with teams ranked in medal positions based on points accumulated.\", \"from\": 2999, \"to\": 3181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3009, \"end\": 3016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_National_Madison_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9651016533664526, \"rank\": 0.03616028064171164, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_National_Madison_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_National_Madison_Championships\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"200 laps\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3031}, {\"ngram\": \"around 31 miles\", \"from\": 3033, \"to\": 3048}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's race\", \"from\": 3056, \"to\": 3072}, {\"ngram\": \"only 120 laps\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3093}, {\"ngram\": \"roughly 18.5 miles\", \"from\": 3095, \"to\": 3113}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 3121, \"to\": 3126}, {\"ngram\": \"medal positions\", \"from\": 3137, \"to\": 3152}, {\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3168}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each sprint rewards five points for first place, three points for second, two points for third and one point for fourth.\", \"from\": 3183, \"to\": 3303, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each sprint\", \"from\": 3183, \"to\": 3194}, {\"ngram\": \"five points\", \"from\": 3203, \"to\": 3214}, {\"ngram\": \"first place\", \"from\": 3219, \"to\": 3230}, {\"ngram\": \"three points\", \"from\": 3232, \"to\": 3244}, {\"ngram\": \", two points\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3267}, {\"ngram\": \"one point\", \"from\": 3282, \"to\": 3291}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Any team that laps a competitor earns an additional 20 points, while 20 points are deducted for any team lapped.\", \"from\": 3304, \"to\": 3416, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Any team\", \"from\": 3304, \"to\": 3312}, {\"ngram\": \"a competitor\", \"from\": 3323, \"to\": 3335}, {\"ngram\": \"an additional 20 points\", \"from\": 3342, \"to\": 3365}, {\"ngram\": \"20 points\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3382}, {\"ngram\": \"any team\", \"from\": 3400, \"to\": 3408}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the final sprint, double points are awarded.\", \"from\": 3417, \"to\": 3464, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the final sprint\", \"from\": 3420, \"to\": 3436}, {\"ngram\": \"double points\", \"from\": 3438, \"to\": 3451}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the individual sprint, a qualification round involving 30 riders will see participants complete three laps of the track, though only the last 200 metres are timed.\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3634, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the individual sprint\", \"from\": 3471, \"to\": 3492}, {\"ngram\": \"a qualification round\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3515}, {\"ngram\": \"30 riders\", \"from\": 3526, \"to\": 3535}, {\"ngram\": \"participants\", \"from\": 3545, \"to\": 3557}, {\"ngram\": \"three laps\", \"from\": 3567, \"to\": 3577}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3590}, {\"ngram\": \"only the last 200 metres\", \"from\": 3599, \"to\": 3623}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 24 fastest competitors then advance to the elimination rounds, where seeded opponents are gradually whittled down to the last 16, then 12, then the quarter-finals, semis and eventually the gold medal final.\", \"from\": 3635, \"to\": 3845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 24 fastest competitors\", \"from\": 3635, \"to\": 3661}, {\"ngram\": \"the elimination rounds\", \"from\": 3678, \"to\": 3700}, {\"ngram\": \"seeded opponents\", \"from\": 3708, \"to\": 3724}, {\"ngram\": \"then the quarter-finals\", \"from\": 3778, \"to\": 3801}, {\"ngram\": \"semis\", \"from\": 3803, \"to\": 3808}, {\"ngram\": \"eventually the gold medal\", \"from\": 3813, \"to\": 3838}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each of the first three elimination rounds (before the quarters) comprises a repechage round, which allows a set number of riders a second chance to advance if they win their heat.\", \"from\": 3847, \"to\": 4027, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first three elimination rounds\", \"from\": 3855, \"to\": 3889}, {\"ngram\": \"the quarters\", \"from\": 3898, \"to\": 3910}, {\"ngram\": \"a repechage round\", \"from\": 3922, \"to\": 3939}, {\"ngram\": \"a set number\", \"from\": 3954, \"to\": 3966}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 3970, \"to\": 3976}, {\"ngram\": \"their heat\", \"from\": 4016, \"to\": 4026}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Four extra places are on offer in each of the first two elimination rounds, while just two advance from the third.\", \"from\": 4028, \"to\": 4142, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Four extra places\", \"from\": 4028, \"to\": 4045}, {\"ngram\": \"offer\", \"from\": 4053, \"to\": 4058}, {\"ngram\": \"the first two elimination rounds\", \"from\": 4070, \"to\": 4102}, {\"ngram\": \"the third\", \"from\": 4132, \"to\": 4141}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the team sprint event, both men's and women's categories field eight teams each, with three riders per team.\", \"from\": 4144, \"to\": 4255, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the team sprint event\", \"from\": 4147, \"to\": 4168}, {\"ngram\": \"both men's and women's categories\", \"from\": 4170, \"to\": 4203}, {\"ngram\": \"eight teams\", \"from\": 4210, \"to\": 4221}, {\"ngram\": \"three riders\", \"from\": 4233, \"to\": 4245}, {\"ngram\": \"team\", \"from\": 4250, \"to\": 4254}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, only the final lap of the third rider is counted once they have got up to speed.\", \"from\": 4256, \"to\": 4345, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"only the final lap\", \"from\": 4265, \"to\": 4283}, {\"ngram\"